defaultThe Additional Written Evidence is a submission by the author in his personal capacity. The Additional 
defaultEvidence presents examination of the 
defaultWorst Case Accident Scenario of bus full of school children being struck by a
default high speed train at an Automatic Half Barrier Crossing
default.  
defaultThe Case study shows that the societal risk resulting from a hazardous event of a train crash into bus carrying passenger
default(s) or workers at Automatic Half Barrier or Full Barrier Crossings or Unmanned Private Crossings are real and fall into intolerable zone. 
defaultThis submission is to be read together with the earlier 
defaultAdditional Written Evidence and 
defaultWritten Evidence SLC 015. 
