default&#xa0;
defaultThe following definition
default of Confidence Interval is taken from the Microsoft Excel package licensed to use by Microsoft to the author. 
defaultBooks on Statistics can also be consulted for verification. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe confidence interval is a range of values. Your sample mean, x, is at the centre 
defaultof this range and the range is x ± CONFIDENCE.NORM. For example, if x is the sample mean of delivery times for products ordered through the mail, x ± CONFIDENCE.NORM is a range of population means. For any population mean, μ0, in this range, the probabilit
defaulty of obtaining a sample mean further from μ0 than x is greater than alpha; for any population mean, μ0, not in this range, the probability of obtaining a sample mean further from μ0 than x is less than alpha. In other words, assume that we use x, 
defaultstandard_
defaultdev
default, and size to construct a two-tailed test at significance level alpha of the hypothesis that the population mean is μ0. Then we will not
default 
defaultreject 
defaultthat
default hypothesis if μ0 is in the confidence interval and will reject that hypothesis if μ0 is not in the confidence interval. The confidence interval does not allow us to infer that there is probability 1 – alpha that our next package will take a delivery time 
defaultthat is in the confidence interval.
default 
defaultTherefore, based upon the alpha of .05 and a three sigma deviation, the confidence interval for the data set of fatalities is computed to 
defaulta mean value of 
default17.78 ± 1.75978
default. 
defaultHowever, 
defaultwe find that range of 
defaultfatalities
default o
defaultbserve
defaultd fall outside this range
default. Therefore, the thesis of 3 sigma deviation is not true. We must seek an alternate figure to satisfy the dispersion in the data. Based
default u
defaultpon the alpha of .05 and 
default80
default sigma deviation, the confidence interval for the data set of fatal
defaultities
default is worked out to a mean value of 
default17.78±
default31.35
